# Wainuia edwardi

| synonyms =
*Paryphanta edwardi
*Wainuia fallai

Wainuia edwardi is a rare terrestrial gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae, endemic to the South Island of New Zealand.
Distribution
This species occurs in New Zealand
Feeding habits
Wainuia edwardi feeds mainly on earthworms.
